        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I am gonna be playing a Necromancer soon.</P><P>I have read and seen many debates reguarding INT or STA which = Hitpoints.</P><P>If Hitpoints are greater than INT then why are so many Magelo profiles strictly INT and very low STA and hitpoints?</P><P>I understand the need for high INT don't get me wrong but I have seen a ton of profiles of level 50+ necros with around 1000 hitpoints with high INT but very few if any items with STA or hitpoints.</P><P>What is the way to go INT or STA and hitpoints. If its INT when do you give up INT for hitpoint STA gear?</P><P>I know this has been hashed out a billion times but as game changes and players grow wiser the thinking changes. So maybe its ok to ask this question again of the learned Necromancers out there.</P><P>My funds are small and I don't want to waste a single plat when I start my character. Or for that matter a singel point when I create my Necromancer.</P><P> </font></td>

