		<a name="62482"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/23/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 13:30:23</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=833"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=833')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=62482&amp;TOPIC_ID=7491&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Int+or+Sta%3F+What+is+the+answer&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         There is debate but here goes.</P><P>Mana per Int points up to 200 is 50% greater then mana for Int points from 201-255.  </P><P>HP = mana for Necros.  HP = life.  The greater your HP the more you can be in lich and the more damage you can take to tap back and subsequently convert back into mana.  </P><P>One stamina point, at level 60 = 2.5 health.  </P><P>Everything is a blance.  Pretty much work on getting your Int to 200.  After that most Necro's work on HP items, some even sacrifice the 200 bottom limit to increase their HP.  </P><P>My thoughts...</P><P>If you have 200 Int and see item A. with 40hp, item B. with 40 mana, or item C. with 5 Sta, go with Item A. - easy one</P><P>If you have 200 Int and see item A. with 40hp/mana, item B. with 40 mana and +5 sta, or item C. with 35 hp/mana and +5 Sta, go with Item C. - with the sta addition, you are getting 50 hp.</P><P>If you have 200 Int and see item A. with 40 mana, item B. with 40 mana and +100 cha, or item C. with +2 str and +20 Sta, go with Item C. - I don't know of an item with +20 sta, but I'd take it.</P><P>If you have 200 Int and see item A. with 10hp, 100mana, and +10 int item B. with 40 mana and +5 sta and resists, or item C. with 35 hp/mana and +5 Sta, go with any, because they are all good.</P><P>Make any sense?</P><P></P><P><BR><center><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95266" target="_blank"><h4><font color=red>Kuotat Smith</h4></a>Baroness <s>Warlock</s> Witch<BR>Mithaniel Marr</font id=red><BR></center><BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

